{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"d5c820bdb0bc9a5cbc4c90b8d34ee19c2ba4a06a6cb1dda8faa4d3a81325ec3f","slug":"papers.network-dynamics.index","location":"/papers/network-dynamics/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Network Dynamics","description":"Neural oscillations, gamma and theta rhythms, synchrony, Hopfield networks, and cortical dynamics.","content_includes_title":false,"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/index-be1853badae5d0d17dd2e42f089ad2cb.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is this domain?","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"ioSgry9zqm"}],"identifier":"what-is-this-domain","label":"What is this domain?","html_id":"what-is-this-domain","implicit":true,"key":"mXzmxmcYJS"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Network dynamics concerns the collective behaviour that emerges when many neurons are coupled together through excitatory and inhibitory synapses. Individual neurons fire spikes, but networks of neurons generate oscillations, transient synchrony, attractor states, and chaotic trajectories — phenomena that have no single-neuron counterpart. Understanding these emergent dynamics is essential for linking cellular mechanisms to systems-level computation and behaviour.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"XyClQpmWHB"}],"key":"Pv0phG4p6P"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why it matters","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"uMfD8tOyIs"}],"identifier":"why-it-matters","label":"Why it matters","html_id":"why-it-matters","implicit":true,"key":"F4WaR3sds0"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The functional states of neural circuits — memory retrieval, sensory binding, sleep-wake transitions, pathological seizures — are expressed as network-level dynamical phenomena. Neuromorphic systems that seek to replicate or interface with these functions must produce or respond to the same dynamical signatures. Attractor network theory, in particular, provides one of the few tractable mathematical frameworks connecting connectivity structure to computational function.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"JaaPzvpchN"}],"key":"q1AwhP5aRB"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core concepts","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"eYSXdh6tRb"}],"identifier":"core-concepts","label":"Core concepts","html_id":"core-concepts","implicit":true,"key":"NBHMYf4Mbj"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Neural oscillations","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"UOqiFj6Q64"}],"key":"r7fPNQQmiu"},{"type":"text","value":" — rhythmic fluctuations in local field potential and population firing rate spanning delta (< 4 Hz), theta (4–8 Hz), alpha (8–13 Hz), beta (13–30 Hz), and gamma (30–100 Hz) bands","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"BkkS3Ugj3Q"}],"key":"g3ZZxpPPL9"}],"key":"VS1aH65Lss"},{"type":"listIt